	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=23234&mid=10656249743162>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=23234&mid=10656249743162>Statz Clarifications</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=23234&mid=10656249743162#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Oct 8th 11:10 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=141855><span id= >Sannto</span></a><br><span id=notbold>18 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.74]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I finally had 10 wins in one location (EF). Here's what I had to do to get the (crappy for now) statz on my AUG - which is in my PoP Charm.&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;Keep in mind - I don't have all the answers, but trying to provide a little info.&gt; I'm not sure if everyone hails the same person - or - If I had to hail the Vahl Shir cause I am one.  But I had to hail her (Vahl Shir NPC in EF) 5 times - each time she told me something in red.  I guess you can do that every two wins or just wait until you have 10 wins to do it all at once.  ANyway - after the 5th time I received a message that my statz were upgraded.  Once I received that message, I unequipped my charm and put it back on. Then I had my 2hp/mana.  The statz were good inside and outside the dungeons.<br>So don’t expect to get your 10 wins and have the statz just show up.<br><br>Hope this helped a bit.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>~Another EQ Junkie - Top 5~<br>Sannto 65 Bst<br>Reju 60 Chanter<br>Yosoy 53 SK<br>Shalimarr 51 Druid<br>Snapwigler 46 Cleric</td></td></tr>
