	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=114865><span id=Scholar>cbaaoth</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>18 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.40]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Every 2 adventures you can hail a certain npc at the camp you will gain important information.&nbsp;&nbsp;After the 10th adventure your hail will improve the stone.  If you right click on the stone it will show nothing different from before.  Now take it and any charm (intricate wooden figurine) for example and place it in the bird bath.  Hit combine.  Re-equip the charm and right click stats.  It will now show the stone as an augment.  Click on the augmented link and it will now show the improvement of +2 HP +2 mana.<br><br>From a post below this is how it increases in stats:<br>Max stats: 10ac, 10 to all stats and sv's, 100hp/mana <br><br>10 successes in *one* theme = 5 bits of knowledge from the adventurer stone quest NPC = 1 boost to your augment <br><br>1 boost to your augment = 2hp/mana <br><br>every 10hp/mana = 1 ac, 1 to all stat/sv's <br><br>minimum successes required to max out aug = 500 <br><br>as much as that sounds, it won't take that much time... perhaps a month or two if you're an above-average of a typical gamer (in between &quot;typical&quot; and &quot;hardcore&quot;)<br><br>As of early October Povar has the best player around 175 wins.  As for myself I am at a paultry 25.  Remember, the statement about how long it will take is from a post from below.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Oct  6 15:57:35 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
